v2025.4.12 — back button on About Connect Nest panel + version sync

Adds a small circular icon-only back button to the top-left of the
About Connect Nest panel, matching the look of HA's other panel pages.

Behaviour: history.back() when browser history exists, otherwise
window.location.href = '/' to land on the default dashboard. Covers
both normal sidebar-click navigation and direct-URL access.

Implementation: SVG arrow icon inside .topbar > .back-btn, wired up
via _wireBackButton() called from connectedCallback after _render().
Hover and active states use rgba(127,127,127,*) so the styling reads
correctly in both light and dark themes.

Side fix: the VERSION constant was hardcoded at 2025.4.5 and never
updated, so the About panel hero and footer kept showing the wrong
version while the add-on moved on. Bumped to 2025.4.12 with a comment
flagging the bump-in-lockstep requirement for future releases.

